author: Steve Yates
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2024
content: The product came undamaged and in good condition.  Instructions are just pics but were easy to follow, hardest part is making sure you grab the correct screws for each step.  Its so easy to assembly you'll want to try without the instructions until you grab the wrong hardware and it doesn't fit.I found the product to be rugged and mostly well constructed (see below).  When fully assembled, it seems very strong.  I can easily get on the top without it buckling under the weight.  The walls seem sturdy and do not flex and bow out like many single wall storage containers.  My main concern for the future is if the corners become brittle and break due to UV.Assembly was very easy, except for the hinge insert nuts in the top.  They are poorly attached and will come out easily.  I plan on removing them all and epoxying them in to hold better.Only other negative comment is that there is a small gap where the sides are attached.  When you put the sides together an push them tight, the gap disappears, but comes back when you put in all the screws.  I can see where water could get inside in a driving rain, so I put silicone caulk at these joints, as well as the joints at the floor.  There are also small gaps around the lift supports that mice could enter, so I had to seal these.Overall, I am very pleased with the results and would recommend this product.  For the money spent and time consumed vs building my own, it is a bargain.

author: Anthony Robert Denogean
date: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2024
content: We had ordered two of these boxes during Prime day.  The first one went together nicely and we were happy with the quality.  The lid is a soft open/close lid so that was nice as well.  On the second box, however, the metal frame of the lid was not square on the left side.  Because of this the three holes on the bracket for the hydraulic shock would not line up and could not be attached to the lid.  I emailed Yitahome to see if they could send us a replacement lid and offered to ship the defective lid back.  They simply offered to send us an entire new complete deck box and said we could keep the other one also!!!  What a great company.  I'm not sure what we're going to do with this other box though.  Ill probably experiment with the lid and see if I can come up with a fix and attach the bracket somehow.

author: Amazon Customer
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
content: I originally purchased this item due to the size and the favorable reviews. Upon receiving the item it had a small rip and tear in the box it was delivered in. I checked the item thoroughly and there didn't seem to be anything wrong with item.The directions were fairly easy to follow, but I would recommend putting the sides together upside down on a firm flat surface and then setting the bottom on the connected sides, front and back. Then taken a rubber mallet and snapping the bottom to the sides in that manner. Much easier process. All screws were properly identified and how they needed to be applied.As you can see by the pictures I supplied my unit warped as it was facing the west and recievithe hot sun. I didn't realize how bad it had become until the backside of the top inside metal frame had separated from the formed plastic top. The screws actually were pulled out from the plastic. With this being said I would have done two things to insure this would not have happened.After weeks of negotiating with the maker and supplier of the product they finally agreed to send me an entire new box. I expressed to them how I believed they could make their product better by including side, back and front lockdowns on all four corners to insure the integrity of the box. I took the initiative to put 4" hook and eye attachments on each corner. I would then suggest upon receiving your box that you check each screw in the underside top of the box to make sure they are secure.I was frustrated at first with the company but I stood my ground, always trying to be kind and sincere with the people I was dealing with, until they realized that maybe they could make a better product that won't warp in the hot sun. I reviewed my new box within a month of my first complaint. I am giving them 4 stars for their customer service but I would only give them 2 stars on the box itself until they fix the possible warping. I hope this helps. So far the 4" hook and eye seem to be working. I will let you know after next summer to see if they did the job.

UPGRADED STRUCTURAL DESIGN- Newly designed with a built-in divider and two accompanying slots for flexible position adjustment; The divider can either be used to separate partitions for classification, or be detached to up additional storage space
IMMENSE STORAGE CAPACITY- This XL-sized outdoor storage box features a generous 150 gallon capacity; With dimensions of 54.3"L x 27.2"W x 28.4"H, the deck box offers ample space to accommodate both indoor and outdoor storage, ideal for cushions, tools, etc
EASY ASSEMBLY- Instead of doing laborious snap-on installation, we adopt improved slide connections so you can easily align the positions of 4 panels and slide them into each other; 2 people are recommended for the assembly due to the large size
DOUBLE-WALL CONSTRUCTION- Made from all-weather guard resin that’s rustproof, corrosion-resistant, and maintenance-free; Features double-wall construction for enhanced sturdiness and durability; The wooden texture complements any decor
MULTI-FACETED APPLICATION- This deck box can blend into any yard or patio to store patio furniture cushions, gardening tools, pool accessories, etc.; The top layer doubles as an extra table or stool
sustainability_features:
Recycled materials
Contains at least 95% recycled material.

content: I had a problem where the lid was internally taking on water. The box was dry until you opened the lid and some water would drip down into the box out of holes near the hinges. author: Americraic
date: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
content: Update: The top won’t stay closed unless you use a lock. I would have preferred that when you shut it that it stays down. Therefore, I’m downgrading from 5 to 4 starsI wasn’t sure about the quality given some of the reviews, but I just finished putting it together and I’m pleased. It looks great.Everything fit together as expected. I’d suggest laying it on the side if you are assembling the lid alone. Otherwise, you need two people so that one person can hold in place as you screw. It took me 45 mins to build this alone. I’m sure that I could have done it more quickly, but I did it while watching football.Also, I tried using my electric screw driver, but I don’t think it was as effective. Plan to build this manually.The box itself is more spacious than I expected so I’m happy about that. I like that there are joins to hold the lid. Only time will tell if they last.I’ve owned several Suncast bins in the past that last 5+ years. Only time will tell the durability on this one. It seems sturdy though so I’m hopeful.

author: Amazon Customer
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
content: This out door storge box assembled easily and seemed perfect for the first 6 months or so. Then the lid began to warp so that the edges lifted up a bit while it seated nicely in the middle.  So far no water has leaked in, and if the warping continues there will be a area on each edge in which water will be able to enter.  I am using this as a delivery box at the end of the driveway so that delivery drivers do not have to come all the way to the house, and it suits my needs well.  However if the goal were to keep out all water long term (years) this item will likely not perform.  It is my opinion that as plastic is forever, things made of plastic should be made to last a lifetime.  This item is not.

author: Scott Pellinger
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
content: I had the same problem many complained of that the sides did not want to just snap into the base as the instrictions indicated.  But the other reviews were right. turn it upside down and use a 2x4 and rubber mallet and they do then snap right in.  Also if putting the lid on by yourself lay it on the ground with the top side down, install the hinges & lit struts on the container first, turn the container on its side so the hinges line up with the holes on the lit and attach the lid first to the hinges then to the struts put screws in all the way but not tight, when all the screws are in place flip it up and then tighten everything up to finish.  Seems like a really good storage container once you get the assembly out of the way.

author: sai60zero
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
content: After a few months of having this deck box, it's pretty good to me so far. It has very good storage capacity. Its closing and locking mechanics are well made and versatile. The only things hindering this box from being perfect are that after a few months of keeping it outside, directly exposed to the elements, the lid has bent slightly due to prolonged sun exposure and its compatibility with locks is limited. That doesn't mean it doesn't protect everything inside from the outside weather as it still does that fine, even with this hiccup. As for the locking compatibility, you need a slightly smaller than your conventional padlock size to go with the locking rings on this box. Even so, it's still an overall solid deck box at the end of the day.

content: This was a giant pain to build. It didn't want to snap together..ended up having to use a mallet to bang it together and dented the edge. author: Andrew Freeman
date: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2023
content: This unit is sturdy, and feels strong. My biggest issue was assembly was not accurate. A tip I found online was to flip the walls upside down and hammer (Use a towel to soften the blow) the base into the sides. That worked a lot better than trying to snap them into place which didn't work at all.Assembly aside, it is definitely solid and looks nice. The front wall does seem to be bowing out a bit, but I think I can fix that. I got the largest size considering I have a large couch with cushions. Overall, if you need the space for cushions, this will be a fine option.

author: D Coombs
date: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2024
content: I ordered this box and it came with damaged packaging which meant it was missing some parts.  My only option with Amazon was to return the box, which would have been a hassle and waste (I already had it mostly assembed before noticing that one of the hardware packets were missing).  I reached out to the maufacturer and they tooke care of the issue directly.The box is well made and was relatively easy to assemble.  The box is heavy, I am almost 60 and, although it was clumbsy, I was able to move the pacakged box myself and assemble the box myself.  There are a couple of steps of attaching the lid hinges and hydrolics that would be much easier with two people, but managable with 1.  Total assembly time was ~30 minutes.I would not expect the box to be waterproff in standing water more than about 1/4 inch deep.  The design does make it pretty water resistent in even heavy rain.  If you don't put something in the locking mechanism (I am just using a bolt as I don't need it to be secure) the lid can open in heavy wind.Overall a solid product.

The media could not be loaded.
                



I was worried because of some of the reviews but I got it and let it sit through a harsh winter in the woods before I reviewed. You can see how much snow I got but still everything was perfectly dry inside not a drop of melted water! I think it’s excellent value and fits snug with a soft open/close lid .. take time in building it right and it shouldn’t leak. You can sit on it too it’s very solid. My only advice is if you have a little sitting water from rain on top wipe it off first because when you open the lid a little will drip in as it opens but it’s a small thing considering the quality and price. I’m waiting for them to come back in stock as I ordered the 90 but might treat myself to the bigger one since it’s only sale and only about 25 more! I highly recommendIt’s got some dirt on it from the winter but easily wipes off and looks brand new when I clean it but wanted to show you after a hard storm how it held up

content: We ordered this box because our packages got stolen. We opted for this one because of overall decent reviews and speed of delivery compared to other sellers. Retrospectively, this was our worst decision, because it is not worth it. It is fairly lightweight, it does not feel sturdy. It requires purchase of a separate lock, but it was difficult to find a lock that would fit through the whole (it needs to be fairly skinny). We ended up finding one also from Amazon, but unfortunately, it requires an unusual sliding motion to be opened, which leads to the majority of couriers (including many Amazon couriers) leaving packages behind the box or by the door, which defeats the purpose of even having it. Additionally, it is fairly difficult to open, so even when a courier makes an effort to open it, they grab it by the "deliveries" sign which pops off every time, and we are too tired of this to keep putting it back in. This is our only purchase from Amazon on which we have so many regrets about buying it, and it feels like a huge waste of money. We are happy for those whom it works for, but for us, it ended up being a waste of 100$.

author: Mark M
date: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
content: UPDATE: EVERYTIME the wind blows decent the entire top (top, side panels and door) blow right off of the base! This has become an extreme waste of money. It doesn't keep packages dry and definitely not secure. Not sure why they put a locking door on this thing when it lifts right off the base. DON'T BUY IT!It's been about a few weeks since putting this thing  together and the side panels are already separating from the bottom. I noticed upon assembly that the little tabs that snap the side panel into place on the bottom panel barely do! I figured maybe the weight of completed assembly would secure it....it doesn't. Now a strong wind or getting bumped the wrong way and it wants to completely separate from the bottom. Also seems kind of pointless to have a lock on it when all you have to do is lift the entire cabinet off the base and access whatever is inside!  Looks great but seems poor quality on the plastic molds. Might have to try and use some sort of adhesive to keep it together. Expected more for the money.

author: Jon R
date: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
content: I have wanted something like this for awhile for packages. When it showed up in the recommendations and the price for it, I jumped on it. Received it today and set it up. It's not as light as others have posted, but a patio brick wouldn't hurt if it's out unprotected. Mine will be on the porch with railing, so I'm not worried. The grandkids wanted to hide in it and the bottom came un-snapped and the top is friction fit. I wanted to make it hold up a long time and not planning on taking it apart anytime soon. So I added some screws to keep snaps in and hold the top. Another review said the handle is hard to open. I agree and added my own high for the delivery person. I also added a bungee cord to close the door and painted the sign to make it nicer and unique. Solid 4.5 stars, but with some screws, it's a 5 all the way.

author: Sukrit Suresh
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2024
content: We ordered this box because our packages got stolen. We opted for this one because of overall decent reviews and speed of delivery compared to other sellers. Retrospectively, this was our worst decision, because it is not worth it. It is fairly lightweight, it does not feel sturdy. It requires purchase of a separate lock, but it was difficult to find a lock that would fit through the whole (it needs to be fairly skinny). We ended up finding one also from Amazon, but unfortunately, it requires an unusual sliding motion to be opened, which leads to the majority of couriers (including many Amazon couriers) leaving packages behind the box or by the door, which defeats the purpose of even having it. Additionally, it is fairly difficult to open, so even when a courier makes an effort to open it, they grab it by the "deliveries" sign which pops off every time, and we are too tired of this to keep putting it back in. This is our only purchase from Amazon on which we have so many regrets about buying it, and it feels like a huge waste of money. We are happy for those whom it works for, but for us, it ended up being a waste of 100$.

author: Sukrit Suresh
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2024
content: We ordered this box because our packages got stolen. We opted for this one because of overall decent reviews and speed of delivery compared to other sellers. Retrospectively, this was our worst decision, because it is not worth it. It is fairly lightweight, it does not feel sturdy. It requires purchase of a separate lock, but it was difficult to find a lock that would fit through the whole (it needs to be fairly skinny). We ended up finding one also from Amazon, but unfortunately, it requires an unusual sliding motion to be opened, which leads to the majority of couriers (including many Amazon couriers) leaving packages behind the box or by the door, which defeats the purpose of even having it. Additionally, it is fairly difficult to open, so even when a courier makes an effort to open it, they grab it by the "deliveries" sign which pops off every time, and we are too tired of this to keep putting it back in. This is our only purchase from Amazon on which we have so many regrets about buying it, and it feels like a huge waste of money. We are happy for those whom it works for, but for us, it ended up being a waste of 100$.

author: Jon R
date: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
content: I have wanted something like this for awhile for packages. When it showed up in the recommendations and the price for it, I jumped on it. Received it today and set it up. It's not as light as others have posted, but a patio brick wouldn't hurt if it's out unprotected. Mine will be on the porch with railing, so I'm not worried. The grandkids wanted to hide in it and the bottom came un-snapped and the top is friction fit. I wanted to make it hold up a long time and not planning on taking it apart anytime soon. So I added some screws to keep snaps in and hold the top. Another review said the handle is hard to open. I agree and added my own high for the delivery person. I also added a bungee cord to close the door and painted the sign to make it nicer and unique. Solid 4.5 stars, but with some screws, it's a 5 all the way.

I got this for outside my apartment door because I order from Amazon daily and was worried about the safety of my packages. The setup was quick and easy with minimal effort. It’s lightweight and was easy for me to move around. I used my power tool just to drill in the screws and the rest you just snap into place. The first day I had it up USPS actually put my packages inside without me having to tell them! Nice because it does say “deliveries” on the front which makes it easier.It’s super roomy, a lot bigger than I thought it was going to be. You can definitely fit a ton of orders in it. I didn’t read the measurements but was surprised at how big it actually was. It does have a latch that you can lock while you’re away, not sure how that would work however unless you gave the delivery person a key. There’s no way to put packages in unless it’s unlocked.The only reason I gave 4 stars instead of 5 is because I’m not sure as to the stability of it. You click the pieces into place and then basically just screw the door on, so if a lot of weight is added to it whether that be the sides or on top I’m not sure how much it could handle.

She is six years old and that was the first time she’s ever done that. So to protect me, I bought one. It is dirty, but I put a paver in the bottom of it . I will take a picture of it later. I recommend this product.

author: Placeholder
date: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
content: This storage locker or secure package locker is super awesome and exactly what we needed. One side has the word “DELIVERIES” which is perfect for deterring porch thieves. We have a home business and at times receive multiple deliveries from all the different carriers. This has already given us more freedom and more importantly,  peace of mind that our important deliveries are safe. Not to mention our miniature dachshunds who do not like people using the doorbell or knocking on the door. It pays for itself in less barking. Anyway, it has some fabulous features such as being weatherproof. We live in an area that receives weather from all four seasons and rain and snow has also been an issue for us in the past. The whole locker is made from super high quality resin. Strong and durable. Heavy duty and build to last. Was easily assembled by one person in approximately 15 minutes. Another great feature is that it has pre drilled holes on the bottom that can be used to easily secure the ground or porch or garage, where ever you may need it. Drill not included. It has a place for a combination lock; then you are able to leave the lock combination in your special delivery instructions. Lock not included. Will be using this with Amazon Key feature that allows delivery drivers to access your garage. Super spacious inside and able to accommodate a few days worth if needed. And still some space to leave your delivery drivers a treat or bottled water. Perfect. Super happy. 60 gallon capacity. Would definitely highly recommend this super useful and super high quality delivery locker. Overall, we are giving this modern and easy design ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️.

author: Scott
date: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
content: This storage box is not just for packages.It was super easy to assemble, and keeps the rain out. The door operates smoothly, and it is easy to toss a padlock on it.I'm using the box to store a couple 5 gallon buckets and a couple bags of food for the wildlife. Bird seed, cracked corn, black oil sunflower seeds, peanuts, and dried corn on the cob for the stellar jays and squirrels, enough for everyone.The door is secure enough to keep the riff-raff out (raccoons), but if it was on a porch with packages, a person could easily get into it if they wanted. -or just pick up the whole thing and run with it.It assembles easily, keeps out the rain, it a good size for packages and critter food, keeps out raccoons, and is as strong as you would expect a plastic storage box to be, and it is easy to throw a padlock on it.

content: I purchased this for outdoor use. It was easy to assemble and had more room than I needed. I was very happy at first. However, if you intend to utilize this bin as outdoor storage and your area has heavy rain, then you could see leakage like I did.I tried to return the second one I ordered--which I ordered during storm not knowing the faults--but they wanted me to self-ship. The UPS shipping was quoted as $242. So, I kept the second bin and gave it away to a family member and ate the $300 for the bin.

content: We purchased 2 of these to store pool toys and towels. We completely followed the directions that came with these outdoor storage boxes. We expected more from the manufacturer since the problem is a defect in the top itself!

author: Amazonfinds
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2023
content: This deck box has high quality plastic and solid corner connections, but unfortunately that's where the goodness ends. The side walls are supposed to snap into the bottom board, but getting them to actually snap in all the way proves impossible. Using a rubber mallet to lightly tap the wall into the base board reveals the inferior construction of the wall for vertical force – the walls easily break and splinter. Because the walls are not strongly connected to the base, the entire unit is flimsy. For example, If you try to pick up the deck box (empty) and move it to another location, the walls will lift out of the base entirely and the whole thing will collapse on itselfHad they simply engineered a better way to attach the walls to the bottom board this deck box would be on its way to becoming one of the best on the market in the mid-budget category. The divider also needs to be improved so that it attaches to the walls using the same strong slide-in mechanism used by the walls when connecting at corners. This would greatly improve the overall stability and strength of the box.This could have been the perfect deck box, but poor engineering of the base and divider make it a completely non-working solution.

author: Amber
date: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
content: Update 2: Seller replied in a timely manner to resolve this issue. Unfortunately, because this is plastic with a reinforced frame sending me a new one would result in the same outcome because of expansion and contraction due to weather. This would be any awesome box if the box material had better expansion and contraction abilities. If kept indoors or used on a climate where the weather stayed pretty much the same it would be a great box.Update: my deck box now has a crack on the corner and the lid does not close tightly. We have not had this 2 months even. After we had our cold spell in Missouri it is now warped as well. I am extremely disappointed in this product now. Everything about size and compacity still stands but right now quality is poor. Contacted the seller so we shall see. As of right now, don't buy the box or plan on keeping it indoors, which defeats the purpose!So my husband and I built a brand new deck and we ended up buying a Polywood furniture set. So we ultimately bought this box to store cushions in. It was the perfect size for the four piece set that we purchased. To give you an idea of how many cushions we had seven seat cushions and seven back cushions and it fit all of them perfectly. It does look nice and it does seem sturdy and I know from the reviews that I read it said that you could sit on it. I am 5'6 and I tried sitting on it and my feet hung a good foot or more off the ground. So unless you're sporting 6 ft tall or more or have freakishly long legs you're probably not going to be using this as an extra seating option. I also don't know how many of these reviews get bumped to some of the other size boxes in this brand but we bought the largest one that you could buy.

content: Upon opening the box, I quickly saw several loose pieces that broken off their corresponding parts. author: Dee
date: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
content: We purchased the deck box and began putting together based on the handbook, which has NO WORDS.So taking it from the front, I snapped together the major pieces, based on a picture on page 5.However, when I turned the page, I saw that there were other parts, not shown on page 5 that should have been assembled BEFORE the major pieces were snapped together.I got on chat with support, and he didn't speak English well, but tried to help me, and after about 30 minutes, told me to that he didn't have an answer.  So I called the phone number, but it went to voicemail. I then wrote out a very detailed email and sent it in, never to hear back from the email. I waited a few days for the never-arriving email, and then called the support line again. This time, the gentleman was very helpful and told me that it was a ONE TIME ASSEMBLY, and solidly put together. He told me to rubber hammer to take the parts apart, and if it breaks then to return it.So we followed his directions, using the hammer and a screw driver, we were able to pound the pieces apart and continued to re-assemble it.We had trouble with the hinges on the lid. The pictures were unclear. We tried installing them two different ways, and never got them to work, so we left them out.  :)This box, now put together seems very sturdy (Unsure about the lid!) We hope that it will meet our needs well. It is very sturdy.We had initially wanted to purchase two, but after this experience, we want to purchase one, already assembled, from a local store.... to save my stress level! LOL

author: Cts
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2024
content: This box was purchased last spring for the summer season in Chicagoland and it did the job well. It's huge, fits all of our pillows and has kept them dry.However, during the course of the summer the top warped badly on one end. It warped so far as to break off the screw in post that holds the aluminum straight edge to the top. Additionally, the straight edge was made too long and was just forced it into place during assembly. Over the winter, as the plastic shrank in the cold, both front corners split. The top still closes but but the split corners and the warped top make it more likely to leak in the rain.I cut off the straight edge about a 1/4" on either end so it doesn't press on the edges of the top anymore. I may put right angle braces on each corner and a screw down through the top to make it conform to the aluminum bar across the front edge which will make the top sit flat against the sides again.Overall, we're happy with the box, just not sure how long it will last on a sunny deck where, I'm guessing, where most people will put it.

author: Mosaic lover
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2024
content: We bought both 30G and the larger deck box and find both to be sturdy, attractive and if it wasn't for the installation instructions would probably give it 5 stars. We hope the manufacturer will promptly revise the installation instructions! We will describe the current problem, which would be really very easy to correct!The individual parts all have inside and outside surfaces. One would naturally assemble the parts so that their inside faces will be inside and vice versa, the outside faces would be outside as they are nicely finished.HOWEVER - what the instructions FAIL to mention is that one part (part D) cannot fit unless it is oriented in the opposite way: this part only must be installed with its outside facing inside!  I wish the instructions would have mentioned this very non-intuitive detail. This would have saved us long and frustrating installation. In fact we were ready to return the product! One such comment and a better diagram could be easily added! Another more minor issue is that the phone number provided for customer services is wrong!

Not only is it humongous, but also a total waste of space because when we fill it up the sides start to separate.Don’t know if we are doing something wrong, but if I could return it, I would go for two smaller size bins.

author: Dana Walker
date: Reviewed in the United States on June 12, 2023
content: 2 D instruction booklet with drawn examples was very difficult to understand. Watched a youtube video at least a dozen times. You cant tell from either which way the pieces are turned. After putting together and taking apart by myself at least 6 times, I finally figured it out on my own. It goes together easily if you can figure out the process and the order that they go together!  I finally got ready to put the lid on only to discover that the aluminum brace bar for the lid wasn’t in the box!!!  Sheesh. What a pain. It actually made me angry to realize how easily it actually goes together. Printed pictures were no help and video had no verbal instructions, just music. The only useful part of the booklet was in identifying the parts and how many are SUPPOSED to be there. Count everything before you start

date: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2024
content: Bought this for our deck to store our patio cushions and things in.  Wanted something large enough to hold alot and be waterproof as we live in a fairly rainy area.I would say it isn't 'difficult' to put together, you could certainly do it with one person, though two makes it easier.  Just go slow, make sure things are aligned and follow the directions.  A rubber mallet certainly came in handy.Once its assembled it is very very sturdy.  My kids can climb all over it and in it with no issues.  The pneumatic hinges make opening and closing the lid easy as can be.About the weather proofing.  The lid certainly closes and keeps rain out.  However the big isn't sealed tightly shut. Because of the fact that it is plastic panels snapped together, there are naturally small gaps here and there, particularly around the base and underside.  If you have adequate drainage under and around it, no issues, but water could conceivably seep in.  And bugs can certainly find their way in, but if u are just looking for something to keep the rain at bay and keep things generally dry, this works great.All things considered, I think its a great value for the money and would buy one again.  I can see it lasting a long long time.

author: Jeff Jacob
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2024
content: Perfect example of why you wait to leave reviews. We purchased the YITAHOME XXL 230 Gallon Large Outdoor Storage Box on May 4, 2023. Early March 2024 (after Winter) we discovered one of the corners had a blow out. After reading some of the other reviews we discovered this is a common issue with this product that costumer service has had to deal with. In some cases they sent a replacement. NOT in our case. They replied as follows:Sorry for this issue, but we currently do not have this lid in stock and the warehouse doesn't allow us to split other items. How about we refund you 55$ to try to fix it locally? Is that okay for you? Look forward to your reply.My reply back was a follows.Its apparent that your company is allowing a defective product to be manufactured. This defect should be recalled. After reading costumer feedback and reviews i find this to be a common issue with this box.  I'm asking for a refund or full replacement.  As $55 is not nearly enough to fulfill repair costs in this economy. The time and inconvenience of searching , setting up a repair solution is very costly.Do Better please.Thank you.As of 3/5/24 8:20 am CST still waiting for a response.Update 3/6/24. Seller offered a full refund or replacement. we elected for the replacement box. +1 starr added. Will update my review after it arrives safely.Update 3/15/24 New box arrived safely, Assembly went quickly, I cut about 1/8 - 3/16 off each end of the upper lid support bar in hopes of this defect never happens again. +1/2 starr.

author: Richard K.
date: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2024
content: I recently purchased a seventy-five foot steel garden hose and I wanted something to store it in as I did not want a wind-up hosemobile.  This Vitahome 30-gallon deck box is the perfect alternative. This container is made out of lightweight plastic so if you're looking for something more heavy duty search on.  With the hose being heavy as it is I don't have to worry about the box taking off in the wind.  Assembly is easy.  Simply follow the instructions while snapping the letter-coded pieces together.  For a personal preference I might drill holes in the bottom corners to drain any water leaking from the hose.  Looks great too, kind of matches my siding.  I was unable to find a lock for the unit's small hole.  The one I purchased along with this from Amazon was too big and the two that I bought at my local big box store did not fit either and were returned.  Finally, the unit seems to be waterproof as advertised.  Mine sits outside by the faucet but on that side of the hose there is no gutter so the rain just bounces off the lid.  Highly recommended.

author: Dale Newcomb Jr.
date: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2024
content: After having a set of patio furniture cushions ruined by the Winter weather in Boston, we wanted something to store them in that was reasonably attractive. This item was just right for our needs as it is spacious enough to fit all of our cushions in the Winter and various lawn games and fire pit tools during the Summer. Building it was fairly easy with two people (one may have been tough in a few spots) and it was lightweight enough to be able to move it around until we found a good spot for it.The only thing I wish was better is the lid, but it is a minor issue. It works ok with the pneumatic hinges but if you don’t lift and close it by the center, the lid bends a bit. It has some metal bars across some of the sides for stability and it feels like if there were another one in the lid, that would keep it from bending. May not be an issue but I just don’t know how the bending would be over time, so we are trying to remember to use the middle each time.

author: John M
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
content: I came across this outdoor box and was almost immediately thinking of things I could use it for.  I've got yard tools, gardening tools, tabletop tools, etc., all in my backyard that need somewhere to be stored when not in use.  Perfect!  Then it came in...So after assembling this thing my plans changed.  We'd had a few packages delivered just close enough to the edge of our porch to get the exterior package damaged.  Nothing major, but enough of a concern to want to address it.  After assembling this outdoor box, we had our answer.  Staging on the front porch, next to the door, was easy - Even when fully assembled the box is light enough to move around by hand, yet heavy enough to not get pushed around with my leaf blower.  Once in place, we tested with the next few deliveries from Amazon -- Each one was placed gently into the box with no issues.  I even had one longer package (the box was ~ 3 ft tall) get placed into it -- Yeah, it didn't close, but the packages were all together.In this day and age, we've seen issues with package theft all over the news, YouTube, Facebook, Nextdoor, etc.  So when I was assembling this, and saw that it had the lock functionality as an option, I both smiled and frowned.  I appreciate that it's an option, but I hate to have to think about it that way.  We kept the kit but did not install it for now.Overall, this has worked out much better than expected.  As mentioned, I was going to use it to hold gardening supplies, yard tools, etc; but decided to go with this as a package holder instead.  I'm very pleased with how it turned out.Pros:- Lightweight for placement, but not so much that the wind can easily take it- Easy to assemble- Comes with a kit for adding a lock- Large capacityCons:- I have no complaints about this box.We're considering purchasing another one for my Mother-in-Law's deck (completely uncovered) so that her packages don't get damaged in the rain.

author: vallightful
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2024
content: I really like my new 150gal deck box. It looks nice, is roomy and all my cushions fit nicely. The assembly instructions were a bit confusing and I reached out to their customer service through the Amazon app. I had a problem connecting the bottom panel with the front and back panels. After going back and forth several times with their very kind and patient customer service they finally reached out to their warehouse who took actual pictures to send me. The problem, I discovered, was that the side of the bottom panel with the embossed C was pictured on the OUTSIDE of the box in the instructions, when it is supposed to be INSIDE the box after assembly. I also was trying to fit both tabs on the edge into what I thought were 2 slots in the other panel but there is only one slot for one of the two tabs to fit into. It's a little counterintuitive but it's because of the design. If you look carefully at the instructions you can see this on a tiny inset, but I was just really thrown by the C panels being upside down in the instructions. Once I got this figured out, assembly was fairly easy by myself but it would've been faster and easier with two people as others have suggested. Yitahome offered me some money back on my purchase for all the trouble and said they would address the problem with the instructions. That is excellent service. I have not had the box for long so I cannot judge its durability but I would not hesitate to buy products from them again, as I believe they would satisfactorily address any problems.

author: GoTurner
date: Reviewed in the United States on March 31, 2024
content: It took us a few minutes to figure out how to connect the first three pieces together as the side pieces have the rough, carved out part on the inside, but connect with the smoother part, which is the bottom interior of the box. So the bottom inside of the box looks like the outside. This way it has a nicer interior finish. Once we figured this out, the remainder of the assembly was straight forward. We have found that this 30 gallon size is a perfect size for, functioning well and not overbearing at all. The color coordinates with our house tones too.At first I wasn't going to get a sign, but after several issues with my paper sign, sanity told me it was worth the investment, which it has been. We have a nice covered porch protected from the elements, but this deck box sits right next to our front door, easily accessible, as well as now being a convenient spot for setting my purse, bags, etc., while opening or closing the door. Plus the deck box provides an extra seat if our porch swing is already occupied.I now wonder why I didn't order this deck box sooner. So if you're on the fence regarding a this, I believe that you'll be glad you did, as it has so many practical uses and has made our life easier.

author: Music lovin' mom
date: Reviewed in the United States on April 18, 2024
content: We have a lovely wooded backyard, but with it comes a large family of squirrels who make it their business to scarf food from our birdfeeders and chew through the plastic storage bins in which we store our birdfood on the deck.  My daughter who had a similar problem recommended that we consider a resin deckbox. We looked at several at Amazon, and we liked the looks and size of this one. It is not too large, it is a muted black (like Charcoal gray) and it has a wood grain texture so is a welcome and attractive addition to our relatively small deck.  So far it seems to be a successful way of storing our seed without it being detected by those pesky tree rats, thus we are happy with the product.  We would not hesitate to recommend it to others.UPDATE:  Oh well!  Apparently, I spoke too soon.  We have been away from our home on vacation for just short of a week and were sad to hear from our neighbor that the tree rats have had their way with our deck box. They chewed a substantial hole in the lid, so it seems we are back to the drawing board.

author: gigbooks
date: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
content: Our ‘Big Name Brand’ trash can enclosure was being thrown around (and frequently disassembled) by residuals from hurricanes and winter winds. I decided to give this brand a try as the replacement. It scored a ‘whoah’ out of the box. This is no thin pop-together thing. The hardware is a mix of nylon/plastic and that trusty metal stuff. The the wall, floor, and lid pieces have some serious weight to them. Well beyond their predecessor. No slide & pop connectors for 1/16th thin plastic here. The pieces screw together into embedded threaded nuts and the door hinges feel pretty heavy-duty as well. Overall, very happy with this product.

author: Gage
date: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2024
content: We Purchased this 4 x 6 shed to use as a chicken coop. It states that it is made of resin, which is not  true, resin is a hard plastic.  This is made of cheap plastic like a garage sale sign. (See photo) It states that it has a reinforced floor, which we did not receive. Not only was it made of cheap material and not resin, it is NOT STURDY AT ALL! Many of the parts were missing screw holes, which we had to drill ourselves. Of the screw holes that  were drilled, many were misaligned. We are not idiots. We assemble things all the time we know how to read instructions, This had a ridiculous amount of parts and the instructions were somewhat confusing at times, but however we put it together correctly. Had my nephew not already started assembling it for me it would be returned because the description is very inaccurate as well as embellished. I expected it to be hard resin so I could hang the heat lamp in it during the winter time when it was very cold to keep the chickens warm, There is no way I would hang the heat lamp in this even though they don’t get extremely hot . It would probably melt it. I am sooo disappointed in the quality . One of my worse purchases from Amazon

author: gb
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2024
content: I’ve just finished assembling the shed today. While it was easy to do, I disliked the fact that the plastic parts were not very sturdy. I couldn’t make the sides lock in properly and started gently pushing them to go further in the slots. To my surprise, the plastic started bending inwards. I had to be extra careful to not damage the plastic parts. Also I had originally bought a pretty good padlock for it. Again to my surprise, it did not fit. The hole for the lock is very short and a bit recessed into the front doors. This makes it only possible to use very tiny locks such as the luggage ones. Any decent lock won’t fit on this shed. If you’re hoping to protect the stuff you put in there from theft, think again.I do like that the shed is spacious and easy to assemble.Edit: After a day and about 3 hours in the sun, the lid started bending like a banana. Now I have to figure out how to reinforce it so it won’t bend.Do yourself a favor and get a better shed.

author: DM
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2023
content: Got it today, went together super easy and I'm impressed with the quality for the price.  The two backs and two sides are held together with 18 nylon bolts.  The nuts are molded into the panels and the whole unit is quite sturdy.  The sides also have additional threaded nuts molded in for shelves, or other additions.  I'm using them to attach elastic cords to keep folded up lawn chairs from falling over.  Also, unlike some other brands, this has actual hinges--two for each door and two for the top.  My only minor complaints would be the locking hasp seems to get in the way, and I'll probably take it back off.  Also, the support rod to hold the top open is not super convenient.  Overall super impressed and would definitely buy again.******Been a few years, and bought another one in larger size.  Still goes together simply and everything is good.  Had an issue with a missing part and the company shipped a replace out immediately.

author: Peggity
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2024
content: There are video instructions as well as a booklet with pictures that comes with the shed pieces.  They do not match up as far as sequence of installation.  We had 2 small pieces missing and the only way we could get these parts was to have an entire shed shipped to us (3 boxes over 100 lbs each) and then had to dig through the boxes for those parts and put them back together to return. Time will tell if this product will hold up to the weather in our area.

content: We had an old plastic shed that we decided to replace with a slightly bigger one. The old shed was very sturdy with thick walls. This shed is flimsy in comparison. author: Alex K
date: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2024
content: I thought this would be a great deal but it really isn't. You have to have some power tools and guess where the screws should be drilled. The plastic is thinner than it should be for being an outdoor shed. It won't take much to break into this especially since the back part is just treated cardboard like the kind that serves as the back part of cheap bookshelves. The price of this is far too high for what you get. It feels like the only purpose of this is to put yard tools in to make the yard look cleaner. Maybe if this was like $100 it would be worth it but at $250, no way. It needs to have better materials, better instructions, and be designed to be easy to put together without additional tools.

author: Carolyn

content: Wanted a shed to store folding lawnmower, power washer & extra chairs. Packaged well, nice looking, simple to put together by yourself but not something for heavy duty use. Back panel is a thin plasticized version of corrugated cardboard, only suitable for against a building & easily susceptible to poking or other impact damage. If the back panel were rigid plastic like the other pieces I'd rate it higher & it would be more suitable for different locations. The size was right for my needs & will do for now. I bought it specifically for the medium hight. Did not want tall item & deck  boxes were not high enough to store what I wanted. As mentioned before, would have rated higher if back piece was rigid plastic like the others.

content: This little outdoor storage shed is pretty decent and mostly easy to assemble, but there were some hiccups and the overall sturdiness is questionable. Let's start with assembly.Assembly is mostly easy with self tapping screws and snap together pieces. The major problem I had and reason for 1 star removal, is that one of the sections on the floor piece had an extra knob of hard plastic that clearly isn't show in the instructions and shouldn't be there. There is no way to physically snap the side wall into place with this plastic piece in the way, so I had to use my oscillating tool to cut it off, while being careful not to cut off the locking tab so I could properly secure the sidewall. I have 3 pictures of this. The first is the other side that did not have this issue, then the side that DID have the issue, and the final sight after cutting the extra plastic off. Once I had it corrected I did get the sidewall to snap in place, and moved along with install. My other complain about assembly is that some parts (like the lid latch) are both labelled incorrectly (supposed to be part T, was labelled L) and was physically different than the instructions. Luckily, it was the only part that looked anything like what was needed so we made it work.After assembly, I noted that the doors sag quite a bit - all plastic construction, so I didn't expect it to be perfect, but I have to lift up on the doors to get them to close. Additionally, anything on the inside that is heavy and leaning against the inside wall or the door will cause the entire structure to flex and lean some. Because of this, we decided to use this as more of a deck box than a shed. We have it on our screened in porch and will use it to store stuff that would normally be on the porch, not "shed" things like lawn tools or anything like that.This shed might work out as a good buy in the long run, but initial impressions are mixed and the frustration of not being able to get beyond step 2 without breaking out the cutting tools was a a real downer. Some of the other sizes might be better, but this size, while passable, isn't fantastic. YMMV.

author: Jill Carabeau
date: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2024
content: The storage shed took me about 30 minutes on my own to assemble. There were two screws in the corners that went through several layers of plastic that I was unable to do by hand with a screwdriver and required a drill. The screws were all self tapping screws and so they were able to drill their own holes through the plastic as only two of the 11 or so screw holes were pre-drilled. I really like the overall look of the storage shed and the top lifting up as well as the doors opening out we're nice design features. However the frame and the structure just are not very sturdy and the shed is incredibly wiggly. I am disappointed with how little rigidity it has. The back wall/panel of the unit is also made from what looks like corrugated plastic. What I mean by this is it looks like corrugated cardboard but I believe it's made out of plastic. It was folded in half in the box and so is not even a solid sheet. I strongly feel that this does not help create much structure.

content: Our ‘Big Name Brand’ trash can enclosure was being thrown around (and frequently disassembled) by residuals from hurricanes and winter winds. I decided to give this brand a try as the replacement. It scored a ‘whoah’ out of the box. This is no thin pop-together thing. The hardware is a mix of nylon/plastic and that trusty metal stuff. The the wall, floor, and lid pieces have some serious weight to them. Well beyond their predecessor. No slide & pop connectors for 1/16th thin plastic here. The pieces screw together into embedded threaded nuts and the door hinges feel pretty heavy-duty as well. Overall, very happy with this product.

author: Gage
date: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2024
content: We Purchased this 4 x 6 shed to use as a chicken coop. It states that it is made of resin, which is not  true, resin is a hard plastic.  This is made of cheap plastic like a garage sale sign. (See photo) It states that it has a reinforced floor, which we did not receive. Not only was it made of cheap material and not resin, it is NOT STURDY AT ALL! Many of the parts were missing screw holes, which we had to drill ourselves. Of the screw holes that  were drilled, many were misaligned. We are not idiots. We assemble things all the time we know how to read instructions, This had a ridiculous amount of parts and the instructions were somewhat confusing at times, but however we put it together correctly. Had my nephew not already started assembling it for me it would be returned because the description is very inaccurate as well as embellished. I expected it to be hard resin so I could hang the heat lamp in it during the winter time when it was very cold to keep the chickens warm, There is no way I would hang the heat lamp in this even though they don’t get extremely hot . It would probably melt it. I am sooo disappointed in the quality . One of my worse purchases from Amazon

author: gb
date: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2024
content: I’ve just finished assembling the shed today. While it was easy to do, I disliked the fact that the plastic parts were not very sturdy. I couldn’t make the sides lock in properly and started gently pushing them to go further in the slots. To my surprise, the plastic started bending inwards. I had to be extra careful to not damage the plastic parts. Also I had originally bought a pretty good padlock for it. Again to my surprise, it did not fit. The hole for the lock is very short and a bit recessed into the front doors. This makes it only possible to use very tiny locks such as the luggage ones. Any decent lock won’t fit on this shed. If you’re hoping to protect the stuff you put in there from theft, think again.I do like that the shed is spacious and easy to assemble.Edit: After a day and about 3 hours in the sun, the lid started bending like a banana. Now I have to figure out how to reinforce it so it won’t bend.Do yourself a favor and get a better shed.

author: DM
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2023
content: Got it today, went together super easy and I'm impressed with the quality for the price.  The two backs and two sides are held together with 18 nylon bolts.  The nuts are molded into the panels and the whole unit is quite sturdy.  The sides also have additional threaded nuts molded in for shelves, or other additions.  I'm using them to attach elastic cords to keep folded up lawn chairs from falling over.  Also, unlike some other brands, this has actual hinges--two for each door and two for the top.  My only minor complaints would be the locking hasp seems to get in the way, and I'll probably take it back off.  Also, the support rod to hold the top open is not super convenient.  Overall super impressed and would definitely buy again.******Been a few years, and bought another one in larger size.  Still goes together simply and everything is good.  Had an issue with a missing part and the company shipped a replace out immediately.

author: DM
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2023
content: Got it today, went together super easy and I'm impressed with the quality for the price.  The two backs and two sides are held together with 18 nylon bolts.  The nuts are molded into the panels and the whole unit is quite sturdy.  The sides also have additional threaded nuts molded in for shelves, or other additions.  I'm using them to attach elastic cords to keep folded up lawn chairs from falling over.  Also, unlike some other brands, this has actual hinges--two for each door and two for the top.  My only minor complaints would be the locking hasp seems to get in the way, and I'll probably take it back off.  Also, the support rod to hold the top open is not super convenient.  Overall super impressed and would definitely buy again.******Been a few years, and bought another one in larger size.  Still goes together simply and everything is good.  Had an issue with a missing part and the company shipped a replace out immediately.

content: Pros - The shipping was fast and on time.  - The storage unit looks great  - Assembly was easy for the most partCons - The only issue I had was the side pieces not sliding all the way into the pre-cut holes that are on the outer rim of the flooring. author: Lamar W.
date: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2023
content: I put this little shed together in one hour. It's sturdy and both doors open and shut easily giving plenty of room to store my 6500 watt generator with room to spare for gas cans. I Installed the generator to allow exhaust out the doors when running!  Raise the top, open the doors for easy access to the generator. Remove the gas cans and open or close the top and I run the generator in wet/dry conditions. There's plenty of space for air circulation and heat escape!  AVOID FIRE HAZARD  !!!  REMOVE THE GAS CANS BEFORE RUNNING THE GENERATOR  !!! !!! AFTER USING,  LEAVE THE DOORS AND TOP OPEN TO ALLOW THE GENERATOR TO COOL DOWN  !!!
